{"body": "@rxaviers Sorry, to clarify, my workaround was to overrride `serializable_hash` in my models, instead of overriding `as_json` in them. This way, when you `:include` other models, their JSON representation *does* get included.\r\n\r\nSo to get a custom JSON representation of a model, and include nested JSON representations of other models, you should override `serializable_hash`.\r\n\r\nThis isn't a fix that can be submitted as a pull request, just a way of working around the issue.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/3131652", "created_at": "2011-12-13T22:17:02Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/2200#issuecomment-3131652", "updated_at": "2011-12-13T22:17:02Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 2200, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nfm/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nfm/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nfm/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/nfm", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nfm/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/nfm", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nfm/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://0.gravatar.com/avatar/c0ccb7ec696d6524e9ee8048835d710e?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Ff6a6a6d5b9feb9c6ce61953f3fd427fd.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nfm/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nfm/received_events", "gravatar_id": "c0ccb7ec696d6524e9ee8048835d710e", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nfm/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "nfm", "type": "User", "id": 127960, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/nfm/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "5238472ebd3543c151011040"}, "id": 3131652, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/2200"}
